snippet.textDisplay: As much as i don't like cars being stored in garages for their entire life and never getting used to their intended potential, in the Sultan of Brunei's case, i think that is what makes them so special. The fact that no one outside of Pininfarina and the Brunei royal family have ever seen these cars, and having literally zero miles on them makes them so much cooler. The best part about the car collection in Brunei is not only the vast expanse and rarity of it but also the entire secrecy surrounding it, just makes for a great research project.

The best part about the car collection in Brunei is not only the vast expanse and rarity of it but also the entire secrecy surrounding it, just makes for a great research project.
